Returning to the child’s stage is an unacceptable humiliation for some people.
“It depends on which person’s abilities,” the psychologist says, “whether he accepts the return.”
According to the opinion of a number of people who deal with palliative care, crucial moments take place at the very core of such a return.
Patients who enter the home with palliative care Victor-Gadbois, all suffer from cancer.
Their prognosis is a maximum of three months of life.
At this stage, a team of doctors and nurses who take care of them does not provide them with so-called "curative" care.
