This is what palliative care looks like when you can’t do anything else.
To make death more comfortable.
Quebec has one bed of palliative care per 11,700 inhabitants.
That's very little if we realize we're all going to die one day.
Here life continues in optimal conditions, explains Dr. Christiane Martel, one of the doctors in the house.
Whether it is a level of physical, emotional or spiritual comfort.
